# Copy to .env and fill in. NEVER commit the real .env -- it is gitignored.
#
# ⚠️  READ THIS BEFORE ADDING A VARIABLE
#
# Vite inlines EVERY variable prefixed with VITE_ into the JavaScript bundle it
# ships to the browser. Anyone can read it with View Source. There is no such
# thing as a "secret" VITE_ variable.
#
# So the rule is absolute:
#
#   VITE_*   ->  public. Assume the whole internet can read it.
#   anything else  ->  not bundled, but this file is still the wrong home for a
#                      secret. Nothing in a frontend project needs one.
#
# API keys, tokens, database URLs and signing secrets belong in the BACKEND's
# .env, behind the server. The browser calls the backend; the backend holds the
# keys. That is the entire point of the split.

# ── The only variable this app needs ─────────────────────────────────────────
# Base URL of the backend API. Public by definition -- the browser has to know
# where to send its requests, so there is nothing to hide here.
#
#   local dev  : http://localhost:3001
#   production : https://www.thewholesaleos.com
#
# In CI this is injected from the VITE_BACKEND_URL GitHub secret, not from a file.
VITE_BACKEND_URL=http://localhost:3001
